    "miapi.help.create": "How to: Create New Items",
    "miapi.help.create.info.0": "First, select the \"Create option\" on the side.\nThis option is only available if there is no item in the bottom slot.",
    "miapi.help.create.info.1": "Second, select the item type you wish to create. Depending on you addons this list may vary. Once you selected an option, you will see the normal module craft screen.",
    "miapi.help.material": "How to: Material Previews and Info",
    "miapi.help.material.info.0": "While replacing a module, you can hover over different materials to see their effects. This also works with recipe viewers like EMI,REI or JEI.",
    "miapi.help.material.info.1": "The material icon next to the slots can be hovered and then scrolled through or shift scrolled through to see all available materials.",
    "miapi.help.material.info.2": "When no item is set into the bottom left slot, you can hover over Materials (also works in recipe viewers) to see stats on the left and special properties on the right.",
    "miapi.help.material.info.3": "BE AWARE that those stats might not correctly reflect stats on the actual module, as the module's specific mechanics can modify the material stats.",
    "miapi.help.modify": "How to: Modify Modular Items",
    "miapi.help.modify.info.0": "To start, you need to put the Modular Item into the bottom left slot to modify it.",
    "miapi.help.modify.info.1": "Then, a list of modules should appear, here, select the module you wish to edit\/replace.",
    "miapi.help.modify.info.2": "Once a module is selected, edit options appear on the left side. The hammer is the option to replace the module with a different one.",
    "miapi.help.modify.info.3": "In the replace option, you now can select the module you want to replace the current one with.",
    "miapi.help.modify.info.4": "Now you are in the crafting option, here you need to fill the Material requirements to be able to press the craft button to replace the module.",
    "miapi.keybinds": "Truly Modular",
